children.text: The ends of the solid joists have not been adequately blocked.
The relevant Australian Standard, AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction, clause 4.2.2.3 Deep Joists that

‘where the depth of floor joists is equal to or exceeds four times the breadth (deep joists), the joists solid blocking between the joists shall be installed between the outer pairs of joists, at not more than 1800mm centres’ .
Solid blocking must be fitted between these joists in accordance with AS 1684.
